WEBVTT

1
00:00:05.161 --> 00:00:07.454
- Got a light?
- Yeah.

2
00:00:10.666 --> 00:00:12.250
Thanks.

3
00:00:12.376 --> 00:00:14.669
- It's pretty. isn't it?
- Yes.

4
00:00:22.929 --> 00:00:25.348
Oh. I'm sorry. Would you like one?

5
00:00:27.892 --> 00:00:31.020
I'll smoke it later when I'm off duty.
Thank you.

6
00:00:31.145 --> 00:00:34.106
You probably have
a couple of roommates. huh?

7
00:00:35.233 --> 00:00:40.029
- Beautiful day.
- Yes. but I think it might rain later.

8
00:00:40.154 --> 00:00:41.655
No. no.

9
00:00:41.781 --> 00:00:44.825
Red sky in the morning.
sailor takes warning.

10
00:00:44.992 --> 00:00:47.035
Red sky at night. sailor's delight.

11
00:00:47.203 --> 00:00:49.205
It was a red sky last night.

12
00:00:49.330 --> 00:00:51.206
I never heard that before.

13
00:00:51.374 --> 00:00:53.667
I learned it in the Boy Scouts.

14
00:00:53.793 --> 00:00:56.337
- You were a Boy Scout? So was l.
- Really?

15
00:00:56.504 --> 00:00:59.381
- Yes. I had 19 merit badges.
- I had 20.

16
00:01:00.341 --> 00:01:04.053
I was working on my 20th when
the government abolished scouting

17
00:01:04.178 --> 00:01:07.931
and sent me into the Hitler Youth instead.

18
00:01:10.977 --> 00:01:15.106
Werner. you think you'll stay
in the army after the war?

19
00:01:15.273 --> 00:01:18.025
No. I'm not a well man.

20
00:01:18.150 --> 00:01:19.985
- And my teeth...
- Your teeth?

21
00:01:20.111 --> 00:01:22.822
Yes. I could tell you
stories about my teeth

22
00:01:22.947 --> 00:01:25.199
that would make your hair stand on end.

23
00:01:25.324 --> 00:01:27.743
Our dentist here is a butcher.

24
00:01:29.203 --> 00:01:31.663
But don't tell anyone I said so.

25
00:01:32.540 --> 00:01:34.917
It's a soldier's right to complain.

26
00:01:35.084 --> 00:01:37.503
Maybe in your army. but here?

27
00:01:38.171 --> 00:01:42.550
One little criticism.
and... to the Russian front.

28
00:01:42.675 --> 00:01:46.136
Is that so? Terrible.

29
00:01:47.096 --> 00:01:49.014
That's terrible.

30
00:01:54.437 --> 00:01:56.397
Werner.

31
00:01:59.150 --> 00:02:01.318
Why don't we go into my room?

32
00:02:01.444 --> 00:02:04.405
I'd better not.
If Strachwitz should see me...

33
00:02:07.158 --> 00:02:09.785
I was just gonna make some coffee.

34
00:02:12.330 --> 00:02:14.290
Real coffee.

35
00:02:42.568 --> 00:02:45.320
Coffee. coffee. coffee.

36
00:02:45.488 --> 00:02:47.406
Where is it?

37
00:02:53.496 --> 00:02:56.790
My grandmother keeps
sending me this stuff.

38
00:03:02.255 --> 00:03:04.715
Oh. yeah. Here. Take one.

39
00:03:12.974 --> 00:03:15.017
Yeah. Keep it.

40
00:03:15.184 --> 00:03:17.102
Nein. I must go.

41
00:03:17.854 --> 00:03:20.523
It's OK. You can keep it. We're friends.

42
00:03:20.648 --> 00:03:23.734
With you in the cooler.
will we be friends? I must report this.

43
00:03:23.860 --> 00:03:29.240
I don't understand you. Report what?
That you and I were chatting in my room?

44
00:03:29.323 --> 00:03:32.117
- I must go.
- Oh. here. It's OK. Look. keep it.

45
00:03:32.243 --> 00:03:35.829
I'll never be able to eat it all.
I've got all I could eat.

46
00:03:35.997 --> 00:03:38.582
I'm sorry. All right. Forget it. Forget it.

47
00:04:11.282 --> 00:04:15.619
And that. I'm sure you'll all remember.
is the voice of the Nelles warbler.

48
00:04:15.745 --> 00:04:19.123
Let's turn our attention to this gentleman -
the masked shrike.

49
00:04:19.290 --> 00:04:21.792
Lanius nubicus. The butcherbird.

50
00:04:21.959 --> 00:04:25.420
The shrike impales his foes
on the spikes of thorn bushes.

51
00:04:25.588 --> 00:04:29.341
Not a very lovable character. you see.
Let's have a look at the colouring.

52
00:04:29.467 --> 00:04:32.928
Uniform black above. from head to tail.

53
00:04:33.054 --> 00:04:38.392
A black rump. a black crown with a bold
white flash. and a white line over the eye.

54
00:04:38.559 --> 00:04:41.353
The shrike lives
in lightly wooded country...

55
00:04:41.479 --> 00:04:45.524
Ah. Hendley. Sit down. You'll find
drawing materials on the table.

56
00:04:46.317 --> 00:04:50.237
The shrike lives in lightly wooded
country. olive groves and gardens.

57
00:04:50.363 --> 00:04:52.823
Well. Hendley. have you
taken to birds too now?

58
00:04:52.949 --> 00:04:55.576
Yeah. Stick around.
You might learn something.

59
00:04:55.701 --> 00:04:58.328
I have better things to do than draw birds.

60
00:04:59.247 --> 00:05:04.543
The voice is a monotonous succession
of scratchy. complaining notes.

61
00:05:04.710 --> 00:05:08.171
Now. let's have a good look at this bird.
He's got a round shape...

62
00:05:28.401 --> 00:05:32.655
An Urlaubsschein. Permission to
cross a frontier. Here's another one.

63
00:05:32.822 --> 00:05:35.115
Which one's the forgery?

64
00:05:36.367 --> 00:05:38.744
- That one.
- That's right.

65
00:05:38.870 --> 00:05:40.621
They both are.

66
00:05:41.163 --> 00:05:44.249
What's holding us up now is
the new form of this travel permit.

67
00:05:44.375 --> 00:05:47.294
- We've no idea what they look like.
- Here's one.

68
00:05:48.963 --> 00:05:51.382
And a military identity card.

69
00:05:52.383 --> 00:05:53.759
And a...

70
00:05:53.885 --> 00:05:55.469
- An Ausweis.
- Yeah.

71
00:05:55.595 --> 00:05:59.515
- Permission to be on Reich property.
- A ticket to Oden.

72
00:05:59.640 --> 00:06:03.685
What appears to be the ferret
assignments for the next week.

73
00:06:04.353 --> 00:06:06.646
You get 10 out of 10 for this. old boy.

74
00:06:06.772 --> 00:06:10.734
- Thank you. sir. Take good care of that.
- Where did you get this?

75
00:06:11.777 --> 00:06:13.737
It's on loan.

76
00:06:15.239 --> 00:06:18.033
In order to get
the right amount of outfits. Roger.

77
00:06:18.201 --> 00:06:21.621
I suggest that we work
mainly from service uniforms.

78
00:06:21.787 --> 00:06:25.582
I can do double-breasteds.
single-breasteds.

79
00:06:25.708 --> 00:06:28.627
and rather nice lounge suits.

80
00:06:28.753 --> 00:06:31.380
Lapels. I can do quite a lot
of things with those.

81
00:06:31.506 --> 00:06:36.135
I can have them deep like that
or high ones like that.

82
00:06:37.345 --> 00:06:40.431
Here's one that
we're working on right now.

83
00:06:40.598 --> 00:06:43.183
Oh. yes. What about buttons?

84
00:06:44.310 --> 00:06:48.939
Take a look at those.
Here's one that I've finished. Roger.

85
00:06:51.067 --> 00:06:57.531
And here's one that I dyed
with a bottle of blue ink.

86
00:06:58.950 --> 00:07:02.161
It's rather good. What's up. Roger?

87
00:07:02.286 --> 00:07:05.289
The goons'd have a field day
if they crashed in on this lot.

88
00:07:05.414 --> 00:07:09.709
That's Sorren's department. Now. I've
started working on the other materials.

89
00:07:09.835 --> 00:07:11.837
This blanket.

90
00:07:11.963 --> 00:07:15.049
Particularly the stripes. Marvellous.

91
00:07:15.174 --> 00:07:16.341
- Coats.
- Yes.

92
00:07:16.467 --> 00:07:19.344
I've got the chaps working on these
all over the compound.

93
00:07:19.470 --> 00:07:22.389
Those battle dresses -
I'm afraid they're a bit too short.

94
00:07:22.515 --> 00:07:27.353
I'll have to get the chaps to make those
into some sort of workingman's outfits.

95
00:07:27.520 --> 00:07:29.730
Blanket ticking.

96
00:07:29.856 --> 00:07:34.569
Now. I've made these into
rather nice little waistcoats.

97
00:07:34.694 --> 00:07:38.239
- Very dapper. yes. Dyed. of course.
- Of course.

98
00:07:38.364 --> 00:07:40.824
Just take a look at this. Roger.

99
00:07:40.950 --> 00:07:46.163
Now. this blanket material. we scrape
this down until it's really smooth.

100
00:07:46.330 --> 00:07:48.540
and then dye it with boot polish.

101
00:07:48.666 --> 00:07:52.628
Corduroy scrounged by Hendley.
I wish we had more of this.

102
00:07:52.753 --> 00:07:55.630
- Where in God's name did you get these?
- Hendley.

103
00:07:55.756 --> 00:07:58.049
- Where did he get them?
- I asked him that.

104
00:07:58.176 --> 00:08:00.887
- What did he say?
- "Don't ask."

105
00:08:00.970 --> 00:08:04.014
Let me show you some of the overcoats
I've been working on.

106
00:08:33.961 --> 00:08:35.921
Good morning. Hilts.

107
00:08:37.632 --> 00:08:40.801
Well. if you're here to find out
if I'm going out again. I am.

108
00:08:40.927 --> 00:08:42.970
- When?
- 17 days. 7th of July.

109
00:08:43.137 --> 00:08:44.930
- Dark of the moon.
- Correct.

110
00:08:45.056 --> 00:08:47.516
Is Ives going with you?

111
00:08:47.642 --> 00:08:50.394
Yeah. if he wants to.

112
00:08:50.520 --> 00:08:53.940
You know that Ives is close to cracking?

113
00:08:55.107 --> 00:08:56.983
Yeah.

114
00:08:58.277 --> 00:09:01.697
- Better for him to go out in the tunnel?
- Safer.

115
00:09:07.453 --> 00:09:08.620
Right.

116
00:09:10.873 --> 00:09:14.543
It's possible for one man to get out
through the wire. even get away.

117
00:09:14.669 --> 00:09:20.257
but there are in fact a considerable
number of people besides yourself

118
00:09:20.383 --> 00:09:22.635
in this camp who are trying to escape.

119
00:09:23.761 --> 00:09:25.679
I appreciate that.

120
00:09:28.266 --> 00:09:30.226
Something's coming - I can feel it -

121
00:09:30.351 --> 00:09:33.937
and it's coming right around the corner
at me. Squadron Leader.

122
00:09:34.063 --> 00:09:36.315
- My name's Roger.
- All right. Roger.

123
00:09:36.440 --> 00:09:38.817
Yours is Virgil. isn't it?

124
00:09:39.986 --> 00:09:42.655
Hilts. Just make it Hilts.

125
00:09:43.823 --> 00:09:47.993
Yes. well. as I was saying. Hilts.

126
00:09:49.328 --> 00:09:52.164
we have maps of Germany -
general maps. that is.

127
00:09:52.290 --> 00:09:56.460
We have all the information we need
for the escape routes out of Germany.

128
00:09:56.627 --> 00:09:58.754
But what we do not have...

129
00:09:58.880 --> 00:10:02.341
Is a clear idea of what's 500 yards
beyond those trees.

130
00:10:02.466 --> 00:10:05.302
We've tried every goon in the camp.
No go.

131
00:10:05.469 --> 00:10:09.181
We must know the exact position
of the local town.

132
00:10:09.724 --> 00:10:12.226
We want to know where
we hit the main roads.

133
00:10:12.351 --> 00:10:15.979
Where the police stations are.
where they've got their roadblocks.

134
00:10:16.105 --> 00:10:20.567
And most important of all.
we've got to know how to get from here

135
00:10:20.693 --> 00:10:23.153
to the railway station.

136
00:10:23.279 --> 00:10:26.740
No. Absolutely not.
When I get through that wire.

137
00:10:26.908 --> 00:10:29.493
I'm not gonna be
making maps for you guys.

138
00:10:29.619 --> 00:10:35.249
I'm gonna be so far away. you won't hear
if they're shooting at me with howitzers.

139
00:10:35.374 --> 00:10:38.168
- Understandable.
- Completely.

140
00:10:40.588 --> 00:10:43.007
I mean. I'd like to help. but...

141
00:10:46.552 --> 00:10:48.971
Interesting idea.

142
00:10:49.096 --> 00:10:52.307
- How many you taking out?
- 250.

143
00:10:55.061 --> 00:10:57.104
250?

144
00:10:57.230 --> 00:10:59.148
Yeah.

145
00:10:59.732 --> 00:11:01.734
You're crazy. You too.

146
00:11:01.859 --> 00:11:05.362
250 guys just walking down the road.
just like that.

147
00:11:05.488 --> 00:11:09.366
Well. some on the road. some by train.
some cross-country.

148
00:11:09.492 --> 00:11:11.827
They'll have forged papers. clothes.

149
00:11:11.953 --> 00:11:13.871
maps. compasses. rations.

150
00:11:13.996 --> 00:11:16.832
You're gonna alert
every goon in the country.

151
00:11:16.958 --> 00:11:20.086
Anybody that can carry a pitchfork
is gonna be out looking for you.

152
00:11:20.211 --> 00:11:25.174
They're gonna swoop down and scoop
you up so fast it'd make your head swim.

153
00:11:27.969 --> 00:11:29.887
Yes. well. thanks. anyway.

154
00:11:30.012 --> 00:11:33.265
- If I can help on the tunnel. let me know.
- That's good of you.

155
00:11:33.391 --> 00:11:35.351
Any time.

156
00:11:36.727 --> 00:11:42.065
Wait a minute. You aren't seriously
suggesting that if I get through the wire

157
00:11:42.191 --> 00:11:45.235
and case everything out there
and don't get picked up.

158
00:11:45.361 --> 00:11:48.155
to turn myself in
and get thrown back in the cooler

159
00:11:48.281 --> 00:11:50.700
so you can get the information you need?

160
00:11:50.825 --> 00:11:55.496
Yes. One has to ask some very
strange things in the job I have.

161
00:11:55.621 --> 00:11:58.790
- We'll give you a front place.
- I wouldn't do that for my own mother.

162
00:11:58.916 --> 00:12:00.751
- I don't blame you.
- Well. OK. then.

163
00:12:00.877 --> 00:12:03.754
- It's completely understandable.
- Well. OK. then.

164
00:12:06.299 --> 00:12:08.259
Yes. well. thanks. Hilts.

165
00:12:15.683 --> 00:12:17.643
Check.

166
00:12:20.605 --> 00:12:22.398
Herr Hendley. l...

167
00:12:22.565 --> 00:12:24.984
Oh. it's all right. Blythe's a friend.

168
00:12:27.987 --> 00:12:31.782
- What's the matter. Werner?
- My wallet. my papers. my identity card.

169
00:12:31.949 --> 00:12:35.118
Gone. I lost them. Everything.

170
00:12:35.995 --> 00:12:37.955
He lost his wallet.

171
00:12:38.080 --> 00:12:41.541
Do you realise what would happen
if Strachwitz found this out?

172
00:12:41.667 --> 00:12:43.752
- The Russian front.
- Dear. dear.

173
00:12:47.006 --> 00:12:49.591
I've looked every place. every place.

174
00:12:50.426 --> 00:12:53.887
I must have lost them while I was in here.

175
00:12:54.013 --> 00:12:56.473
- No.
- Yes.

176
00:12:56.599 --> 00:13:00.352
Look. I told you we were friends.
We'll find them.

177
00:13:00.478 --> 00:13:02.897
Oh. thank you. Herr Hendley.

178
00:13:04.357 --> 00:13:06.025
Werner.

179
00:13:06.150 --> 00:13:09.236
Not now. It might look a little peculiar

180
00:13:09.362 --> 00:13:12.948
if you and I were seen
probing around at this time of night.

181
00:13:13.991 --> 00:13:19.162
Look. I'll find them. I promise you I'll
find 'em if I have to tear this room apart.

182
00:13:25.920 --> 00:13:28.464
- Thank you.
- Forget it.

183
00:13:28.589 --> 00:13:30.007
- Werner.
- Yes?

184
00:13:30.132 --> 00:13:32.467
There is one small favour.

185
00:13:32.844 --> 00:13:35.179
A camera.

186
00:13:36.514 --> 00:13:40.017
We want to take some snapshots.
You know. keepsakes.

187
00:13:41.477 --> 00:13:45.481
35mm with a 2.8 lens and a plane shutter.

188
00:13:45.731 --> 00:13:47.691
Focal-plane shutter.

189
00:13:49.318 --> 00:13:52.863
Werner. that's a focal-plane shutter.

190
00:13:54.115 --> 00:13:55.950
Let me know when you got it.

191
00:14:00.788 --> 00:14:05.417
He's a crazy. mixed-up kid.
that Werner. but I like him.

192
00:14:05.543 --> 00:14:07.503
Checkmate.

193
00:14:31.611 --> 00:14:33.863
How soon's our air pump
going to be ready?

194
00:14:34.030 --> 00:14:37.366
- I'll have it for you tomorrow.
- You're badly behind schedule.

195
00:14:37.491 --> 00:14:39.826
- How's it coming. Danny?
- No good.

196
00:14:39.952 --> 00:14:42.454
- No good?
- Today. three times.

197
00:15:00.181 --> 00:15:01.515
Willie. you all right?

198
00:15:01.641 --> 00:15:03.601
Pull!

199
00:15:32.421 --> 00:15:37.384
You're gonna have to shore up the whole
bloody tunnel. Roger. All 335 feet of it.

200
00:15:37.552 --> 00:15:39.470
Four times today.

201
00:15:40.680 --> 00:15:44.517
This way we never get through.
We must have more wood.

202
00:15:45.560 --> 00:15:48.854
It's a lot of timber. Roger. Can you get it?

203
00:15:51.732 --> 00:15:54.693
We'll get it. We've gotta get it.

204
00:15:55.862 --> 00:15:59.490
I'll put Hendley on it.
and the new man we got this morning.

205
00:16:00.533 --> 00:16:01.659
OK. Willie.

206
00:16:02.034 --> 00:16:05.579
On the first day of Christmas
my true love sent to me

207
00:16:05.746 --> 00:16:08.165
A partridge in a pear tree

208
00:16:08.541 --> 00:16:11.752
On the second day of Christmas
my true love sent to me

209
00:16:11.878 --> 00:16:15.381
Two turtle doves
and a partridge in a pear tree

210
00:16:15.882 --> 00:16:19.010
On the fourth day of Christmas
my true love sent to me

211
00:16:19.135 --> 00:16:21.428
Four calling birds. three French hens

212
00:16:21.554 --> 00:16:25.391
Two turtle doves
and a partridge in a pear tree

213
00:16:25.558 --> 00:16:28.978
On the fifth day of Christmas
my true love sent to me

214
00:16:29.103 --> 00:16:32.106
Five gold rings

215
00:16:33.441 --> 00:16:37.403
- How's it going with the rafters up there?
- Taking out one in four.

216
00:16:43.326 --> 00:16:44.327
Stay with it.

217
00:16:44.452 --> 00:16:47.621
Five gold rings

218
00:16:47.747 --> 00:16:49.707
Four calling birds. three French hens

219
00:16:49.832 --> 00:16:53.502
Two turtle doves
and a partridge in a pear tree

220
00:16:53.669 --> 00:16:57.089
On the seventh day of Christmas
my true love sent to me

221
00:16:57.215 --> 00:16:59.800
Seven swans a-swimming.
six geese a-laying

222
00:16:59.967 --> 00:17:03.053
Five gold rings

223
00:17:03.221 --> 00:17:05.264
Four calling birds. three French hens

224
00:17:05.389 --> 00:17:09.601
Two turtle doves
and a partridge in a pear tree

225
00:17:22.990 --> 00:17:25.909
Five gold rings. four calling birds...

226
00:17:26.077 --> 00:17:29.455
Bloody singing. I've never worked
so hard in all my life. Hi. Hilts.

227
00:17:29.580 --> 00:17:30.581
Say. Cavendish...

228
00:17:30.706 --> 00:17:32.749
Three French hens. two turtle doves

229
00:17:32.875 --> 00:17:34.793
And a partridge in a pear...

230
00:17:34.919 --> 00:17:36.879
Allez hup!

231
00:17:43.427 --> 00:17:45.387
Never mind.

232
00:17:55.398 --> 00:17:58.109
Here's a present from our friend Werner.

233
00:17:58.234 --> 00:17:59.902
Splendid.

234
00:18:00.069 --> 00:18:02.029
Simply splendid.

235
00:18:03.114 --> 00:18:05.282
This should do very nicely.

236
00:18:08.911 --> 00:18:10.704
Those are Ashley-Pitt's men.

237
00:18:10.872 --> 00:18:14.959
He requested permission to dispose
of some of his dirt in our attic.

238
00:19:23.069 --> 00:19:27.323
Tom has reached just beyond
that pile of wood. sir.

239
00:19:27.448 --> 00:19:31.743
- Harry. of course. isn't as far as that.
- How much further to the trees?

240
00:19:31.869 --> 00:19:33.871
We make it 50 feet. sir.

241
00:19:33.996 --> 00:19:37.332
- Dark of the moon is the 7th...
- 8th and 9th.

242
00:19:37.500 --> 00:19:39.418
A day earlier in August.

243
00:19:45.550 --> 00:19:47.468
Morning.

244
00:19:48.594 --> 00:19:50.679
There he goes again.

245
00:19:50.805 --> 00:19:53.349
Why is he buying up all
the potatoes in the camp?

246
00:19:53.474 --> 00:19:56.310
I've been working on that.
but I can't find out.

247
00:19:56.435 --> 00:19:58.979
Hilts and Hendley
lock themselves in every night.

248
00:19:59.105 --> 00:20:02.399
Sometimes Goff's with them.
Other nights he's on guard outside.

249
00:20:02.567 --> 00:20:06.529
Mac. we'll close down Dick and Harry.
Seal them off.

250
00:20:06.696 --> 00:20:09.490
Put the entire effort into Tom
and press on into the trees.

251
00:20:09.615 --> 00:20:11.116
Right. Roger.

252
00:20:59.123 --> 00:21:00.582
Wow.

253
00:21:02.585 --> 00:21:04.211
Wow.

254
00:21:06.172 --> 00:21:07.631
Wow.

255
00:21:34.200 --> 00:21:35.784
Wow.

256
00:21:42.375 --> 00:21:43.959
Wow.

257
00:21:52.593 --> 00:21:53.969
Wow.

258
00:22:44.729 --> 00:22:45.771
About face!

259
00:22:47.023 --> 00:22:48.983
Forward march!

260
00:22:56.199 --> 00:23:00.036
- What is it?
- They're celebrating the revolution.

261
00:23:00.161 --> 00:23:02.121
It's the 4th of July.

262
00:23:11.672 --> 00:23:13.465
What the devil's this?

263
00:23:19.472 --> 00:23:21.599
Gentlemen. you're invited for free drinks.

264
00:23:21.724 --> 00:23:25.477
- A little present from the colonials.
- Down the British.

265
00:23:25.603 --> 00:23:28.105
- Quite right too.
- And a little drink to Tom.

266
00:23:28.231 --> 00:23:30.358
And to getting home.

267
00:23:30.483 --> 00:23:32.067
Very well. We accept.

268
00:23:32.193 --> 00:23:34.028
- Up the rebels!
- Down the British!

269
00:23:34.195 --> 00:23:35.571
Gentlemen. follow us.

270
00:23:35.696 --> 00:23:37.656
About face!

271
00:23:57.343 --> 00:23:59.303
Company. halt!

272
00:24:03.391 --> 00:24:05.726
All right. let's line up down here!

273
00:24:06.811 --> 00:24:09.188
All right. grab a cup!

274
00:24:09.313 --> 00:24:11.273
Line it up! Here we go.

275
00:24:18.406 --> 00:24:21.033
That explains what happened
to the potatoes.

276
00:24:21.158 --> 00:24:24.161
No harm in closing down Tom
for one day. Roger.

277
00:24:24.287 --> 00:24:27.123
I suppose it'll do us all good
to let off a bit of steam.

278
00:24:27.290 --> 00:24:31.127
There's only 14 feet to go. sir. and you
can feel it throughout the whole camp.

279
00:24:31.252 --> 00:24:34.171
- I think that calls for a drink.
- Hear. hear.

280
00:24:34.297 --> 00:24:36.549
- Drink it up!
- What is this stuff. Hilts?

281
00:24:36.716 --> 00:24:39.927
Moonshine.
American moonshine. Moonshine.

282
00:24:40.052 --> 00:24:42.596
Make my moustache grow. Cheers.

283
00:24:42.722 --> 00:24:45.015
Keep it moving.

284
00:24:45.141 --> 00:24:47.351
Hello. Eric. Don't spill any of that.

285
00:24:47.476 --> 00:24:49.853
- There you go.
- Down with the British.

286
00:24:50.188 --> 00:24:53.274
All right. old cobber. Keep it mo...

287
00:24:53.941 --> 00:24:57.110
- Don't get any on your clothes.
- Cheers!

288
00:24:58.112 --> 00:25:01.198
- Don't spill any of that.
- Before your morning tea?

289
00:25:01.324 --> 00:25:03.492
Keep it moving.

290
00:25:03.618 --> 00:25:05.703
Don't get any on your clothes. sir.

291
00:25:05.870 --> 00:25:09.206
American moonshine.
Don't smoke right after you drink it.

292
00:25:09.332 --> 00:25:12.335
No smoking.
No smoking while you're drinking.

293
00:25:27.391 --> 00:25:29.351
Get good and stoned. my friend.

294
00:25:31.729 --> 00:25:33.981
Keep it going. Keep it...

295
00:25:34.815 --> 00:25:38.235
No taxation without representation.

296
00:25:38.361 --> 00:25:40.863
Keep it going. boys. Keep it...

297
00:25:42.323 --> 00:25:44.616
Keep it going. fellas. Enjoy yourselves.

298
00:25:44.742 --> 00:25:47.161
Well. let's drink to Tom.

299
00:25:47.286 --> 00:25:49.246
To Tom.

300
00:25:56.087 --> 00:26:00.424
In the three years. seven months
and two weeks that I've been in the bag.

301
00:26:00.550 --> 00:26:03.553
that's the most extraordinary
stuff I've ever tasted.

302
00:26:03.678 --> 00:26:06.972
- It's shattering.
- Well. I think it's rather good.

303
00:26:09.809 --> 00:26:13.354
Well. with your permission. sir.
I think I'll all on kive.

304
00:26:14.814 --> 00:26:16.774
Call on Ives.

305
00:26:26.325 --> 00:26:28.285
Cheers. Hendley!

306
00:26:36.586 --> 00:26:38.421
You know what that is?

307
00:26:38.546 --> 00:26:40.798
I'll tell you what it isn't.

308
00:26:40.923 --> 00:26:43.258
It isn't Napoleon brandy.

309
00:26:44.802 --> 00:26:46.762
How do you like it. sir?

310
00:26:47.805 --> 00:26:49.723
Well. it's...

311
00:26:49.849 --> 00:26:51.809
To the colonies.

312
00:26:51.934 --> 00:26:53.894
Independence.

313
00:26:59.609 --> 00:27:03.946
How are you managing over there without
us? Getting along all right. are you?

314
00:27:04.071 --> 00:27:07.115
We seem to be getting along all right.
shir... sir.

315
00:27:15.333 --> 00:27:17.752
Yes. well. it's...

316
00:27:19.003 --> 00:27:20.963
It's good stuff. Hilts.

317
00:27:23.299 --> 00:27:25.259
Thank you. sir.

318
00:27:45.571 --> 00:27:47.531
Danny! Here's to...

319
00:27:54.997 --> 00:27:57.582
Roger. goons in 105.

320
00:27:58.376 --> 00:28:00.419
- Who?
- Strachwitz.

321
00:28:03.631 --> 00:28:08.594
We have to ignore it. If we pay attention.
the goons'll know the hut's important.

322
00:28:09.637 --> 00:28:11.555
Here's to going home.

323
00:28:26.571 --> 00:28:29.824
Come on. Danny.
They've searched it a hundred times.

324
00:28:29.949 --> 00:28:31.909
Home!

325
00:28:44.505 --> 00:28:48.467
Anyway. I'm glad we've got you
in the tunnel with us. To Tom. eh?

326
00:28:51.179 --> 00:28:55.057
Och. never mind. You'll be walking down
Argyle Street in a couple of weeks.

327
00:28:55.224 --> 00:28:59.937
To Tom. You know. Sandy.
I'm just beginning to realise that myself.

328
00:29:00.062 --> 00:29:03.023
Why shouldn't you. man?
We're nearly at the trees. boy.

329
00:29:03.149 --> 00:29:05.151
We're nearly at the trees. eh?

330
00:29:52.490 --> 00:29:54.492
Herr Hauptfeldwebel!

331
00:29:55.117 --> 00:29:56.451
Herr Hauptfeldwebel!

332
00:30:35.324 --> 00:30:37.576
Oh. my God! They've found Tom.

333
00:30:51.632 --> 00:30:53.592
It's the tunnel.

334
00:31:10.443 --> 00:31:12.403
Success.

335
00:31:36.302 --> 00:31:37.594
Ives!

336
00:32:48.833 --> 00:32:52.837
Sir. let me know
the exact information you need.

337
00:32:53.921 --> 00:32:56.214
- I'm going out tonight.
- Right.

338
00:32:58.759 --> 00:33:00.802
Open up Harry.

339
00:33:00.928 --> 00:33:03.555
We dig. Around the clock.

340
00:34:38.484 --> 00:34:40.777
- Cooler.
- Right.

341
00:34:44.240 --> 00:34:47.076
Well. I didn't think
they'd catch him so soon.

342
00:34:48.911 --> 00:34:51.038
He wasn't caught.

343
00:35:04.677 --> 00:35:06.929
Hilts. welcome home.

344
00:35:59.941 --> 00:36:01.025
Danny?

345
00:36:03.319 --> 00:36:05.279
Danny?

346
00:36:08.157 --> 00:36:10.117
Danny?

347
00:36:16.666 --> 00:36:18.626
Are you all right. Danny?

348
00:36:20.503 --> 00:36:22.421
Yes.

349
00:36:22.588 --> 00:36:24.506
All right.

350
00:36:26.676 --> 00:36:29.679
All right. Bring some shovels. I'm all right.

351
00:36:32.306 --> 00:36:34.808
For God's sake.
you've left out a whole eagle.

352
00:36:34.976 --> 00:36:36.894
That's impossible.

353
00:36:38.104 --> 00:36:40.022
Yes.

354
00:36:40.731 --> 00:36:43.650
Four days' work up the bloody spout!

355
00:36:44.819 --> 00:36:46.946
I'm sorry. Colin.

356
00:36:47.071 --> 00:36:49.031
It's all right. Smithy.

357
00:36:50.157 --> 00:36:54.035
It's getting late.
You push off to bed. I'll pack up here.

358
00:36:54.161 --> 00:36:56.037
All right.

359
00:36:56.163 --> 00:36:58.874
- Good night. Colin.
- Good night. Smithy.

360
00:37:39.123 --> 00:37:41.416
I can't see a bloody thing.

361
00:38:09.570 --> 00:38:13.532
- Your German's very good.
- Thanks. Mac. I've put in a lot of...

362
00:38:13.741 --> 00:38:18.120
Watch it. That's the easiest way to trip up
a suspect. Don't fall for that old gag.

363
00:38:18.287 --> 00:38:20.914
- I'm sorry. Mac.
- OK. But remember. German always.

364
00:38:34.512 --> 00:38:38.432
One. two. three. four. five.

365
00:38:57.869 --> 00:38:58.870
Roger.

366
00:39:04.041 --> 00:39:05.500
No. it's me.

367
00:39:07.879 --> 00:39:09.881
How do you like the old escape suit?

368
00:39:10.006 --> 00:39:11.966
Fine. fine.

369
00:39:14.343 --> 00:39:16.303
Colin.

370
00:39:18.514 --> 00:39:20.849
How do you like mine?

371
00:39:20.975 --> 00:39:23.310
It looks splendid.

372
00:39:49.795 --> 00:39:52.047
Where are you going?
You'll get yourself shot.

373
00:39:52.215 --> 00:39:56.344
- What's the matter with you?
- I'm going out through that fence.

374
00:39:58.012 --> 00:40:01.557
Danny. we're getting out through
the tunnel. We're almost clear.

375
00:40:01.682 --> 00:40:04.518
Please. Willie. let me alone.

376
00:40:04.685 --> 00:40:07.187
I can't go in that tunnel any more.

377
00:40:07.313 --> 00:40:09.732
So I'm going out through the wire.

378
00:40:13.277 --> 00:40:17.030
Danny. think. We're getting out.
but not through the wire.

379
00:40:17.198 --> 00:40:20.159
We're getting out through the tunnel.
It's finished.

380
00:40:20.326 --> 00:40:22.578
- I go out now.
- No.

381
00:40:23.621 --> 00:40:26.957
Danny. you go through that wire
and you'll get killed.

382
00:40:34.257 --> 00:40:36.217
Don't do that.

383
00:40:38.427 --> 00:40:40.387
Willie...

384
00:40:42.098 --> 00:40:44.266
Since I was a boy.

385
00:40:44.392 --> 00:40:48.813
I hate and feared little rooms.

386
00:40:48.938 --> 00:40:51.106
closets. caves.

387
00:40:51.232 --> 00:40:53.651
Danny. you've dug 17 tunnels.
Over 17 tunnels.

388
00:40:53.776 --> 00:40:56.111
Because I must get out.

389
00:40:56.237 --> 00:40:59.365
I hide the fear. and I dig.

390
00:41:00.449 --> 00:41:04.411
But tomorrow night in the tunnel
with all those men.

391
00:41:04.537 --> 00:41:07.164
I'm afraid maybe this time
I will lose my head

392
00:41:07.331 --> 00:41:10.125
and ruin the escape for everybody.

393
00:41:12.879 --> 00:41:14.839
So I go now.

394
00:41:19.677 --> 00:41:22.596
Danny. I'll see you through the tunnel.

395
00:41:24.015 --> 00:41:27.643
I'll look after you.
I'll stick with you all the way.

396
00:41:29.020 --> 00:41:30.938
All right.

397
00:41:39.197 --> 00:41:41.157
- Good evening.
- Hello. Roger.

398
00:41:42.033 --> 00:41:44.493
Well. how do you think we look?

399
00:41:48.164 --> 00:41:49.999
It's as bad as all that?

400
00:41:50.124 --> 00:41:56.672
Colin. I want first of all to say that without
you. we would not have been ready.

401
00:41:56.797 --> 00:42:00.425
That's all right. I had lots of help.
Lots of very good help.

402
00:42:02.178 --> 00:42:04.138
What's the matter. Roger?

403
00:42:05.264 --> 00:42:07.599
You can't go.

404
00:42:08.184 --> 00:42:10.644
- What do you mean?
- I can't allow it.

405
00:42:10.811 --> 00:42:11.269
Why?

406
00:42:11.395 --> 00:42:14.231
You can't see your hand
in front of your face.

407
00:42:14.357 --> 00:42:16.942
You'd be caught before you got 10 yards.

408
00:42:17.109 --> 00:42:19.027
That's ridiculous.

409
00:42:20.112 --> 00:42:23.448
That's ridiculous. Never heard
anything so absurd in my life.

410
00:42:23.574 --> 00:42:26.952
I can see perfectly. I can see perfectly!

411
00:42:27.620 --> 00:42:31.165
I can see... that pin down there.

412
00:42:31.290 --> 00:42:33.959
- Does that satisfy you?
- What pin? Where?

413
00:42:45.721 --> 00:42:49.015
Colin. do you see the foot of the door?

414
00:42:50.309 --> 00:42:51.601
Yes. of course.

415
00:42:53.771 --> 00:42:56.857
Put the pin down there. will you?

416
00:42:56.983 --> 00:42:58.442
All right.

417
00:43:02.864 --> 00:43:04.323
All right. Come on.

418
00:43:05.199 --> 00:43:07.159
Come on. Sit down.

419
00:43:08.786 --> 00:43:11.288
Sit down. It was a good try.

420
00:43:12.582 --> 00:43:16.627
I hate these last-minute letdowns.
but I've only just been told.

421
00:43:16.752 --> 00:43:20.255
- It's too risky for you.
- Don't you think that's Colin's decision?

422
00:43:20.381 --> 00:43:22.841
- No. I don't.
- Come on. Roger.

423
00:43:22.967 --> 00:43:28.389
We all know the score here.
Well. at least. most of us do.

424
00:43:28.514 --> 00:43:31.683
Your idea of this escape
is to start another front.

425
00:43:31.809 --> 00:43:36.104
to foul up the Germans behind the lines.
All right. that's fine.

426
00:43:36.272 --> 00:43:40.734
But once we get past that wire and have
them looking all over Germany for us.

427
00:43:40.860 --> 00:43:43.279
that mission is accomplished.

428
00:43:43.446 --> 00:43:46.657
Afterwards. we have
some ideas of our own.

429
00:43:47.867 --> 00:43:49.660
You mean getting home?

430
00:43:49.827 --> 00:43:52.162
- Back to your family?
- That's right.

431
00:43:52.288 --> 00:43:55.624
Do you really believe
I haven't thought about that too?

432
00:43:55.750 --> 00:43:57.710
I'm sure you have.

433
00:43:58.920 --> 00:44:00.880
I know Colin has.

434
00:44:01.923 --> 00:44:04.050
And. Roger. I have too.

435
00:44:04.175 --> 00:44:06.135
We think we can make it all the way.

436
00:44:06.302 --> 00:44:11.015
Not Colin. He'd be an appalling hazard
to the escape. That must be my decision.

437
00:44:11.140 --> 00:44:15.269
Let's talk about hazard.
Let's talk about you.

438
00:44:15.394 --> 00:44:19.356
You're the biggest hazard we have.
The Gestapo has you marked.

439
00:44:21.025 --> 00:44:23.318
No one has said you can't go.

440
00:44:24.779 --> 00:44:27.281
That's true.

441
00:44:27.448 --> 00:44:29.741
I have thought about the Gestapo.

442
00:44:31.827 --> 00:44:35.872
But if you're asking me how far
a commanding officer is allowed to go.

443
00:44:35.998 --> 00:44:37.958
or dare go.

444
00:44:39.001 --> 00:44:41.420
or should be permitted to play God.

445
00:44:42.880 --> 00:44:44.798
I can't answer you.

446
00:44:46.133 --> 00:44:47.884
But I can tell you

447
00:44:48.386 --> 00:44:52.014
a blind man is an unnecessary hazard
to himself and the whole plan.

448
00:44:52.139 --> 00:44:55.100
and must therefore be
eliminated from the operation.

449
00:45:06.153 --> 00:45:11.324
Colin's not a blind man as long
as he's with me. and he's going with me.

450
00:45:17.415 --> 00:45:19.667
It's all right with you. Colin?

451
00:45:21.752 --> 00:45:24.337
Oh. yes. Quite.

452
00:45:32.013 --> 00:45:37.768
Very well. I'll arrange for your escape
numbers to be altered accordingly.

453
00:45:38.686 --> 00:45:40.646
Good night. gentlemen.

454
00:45:47.528 --> 00:45:49.446
Actually...

455
00:45:50.656 --> 00:45:52.824
he's quite right.

456
00:45:52.992 --> 00:45:54.910
He's completely right.

457
00:45:55.536 --> 00:45:57.579
I really shouldn't go at all.

458
00:45:57.705 --> 00:46:01.041
My eyes have been getting
worse and worse lately.

459
00:46:01.209 --> 00:46:04.587
I think they call it progressive myopia.

460
00:46:05.171 --> 00:46:08.215
I can see things up here. Close to.

461
00:46:08.382 --> 00:46:10.801
I can see to work. but...

462
00:46:13.721 --> 00:46:16.056
you're just a blur.

463
00:46:16.182 --> 00:46:18.142
I know.

464
00:46:18.976 --> 00:46:21.353
Oh. hell. We'll make it in great shape.

465
00:46:21.479 --> 00:46:23.731
Colin. do you have any tea?

466
00:46:24.857 --> 00:46:27.484
- Yes. of course.
- Then let's have some.

467
00:46:29.070 --> 00:46:31.030
Splendid.

468
00:47:16.951 --> 00:47:19.078
Hi. Hilts.

469
00:47:19.203 --> 00:47:21.163
Hey. Mac.

470
00:47:23.457 --> 00:47:24.916
When?

471
00:47:25.042 --> 00:47:27.627
Tonight. We thought
they'd never let you out.

472
00:47:27.795 --> 00:47:30.255
Me. too. Let's get at it.

473
00:47:30.381 --> 00:47:33.175
- Bartlett's waiting for you.
- I'll be there.

474
00:48:44.288 --> 00:48:45.539
What time?

475
00:48:47.750 --> 00:48:49.835
Only eight minutes now. Danny.

476
00:48:54.006 --> 00:48:55.966
You OK?

477
00:49:06.143 --> 00:49:07.978
Cavendish.

478
00:49:08.104 --> 00:49:09.563
Griff. down there.

479
00:49:09.689 --> 00:49:11.649
Goff. there.

480
00:49:31.586 --> 00:49:34.630
Smith. Foles. third on the right.

481
00:49:35.464 --> 00:49:38.675
Blythe. Hendley. third on the left.

482
00:50:08.456 --> 00:50:09.874
There are the lights.

483
00:50:11.626 --> 00:50:13.961
Right on the tick. Danny.

484
00:50:23.429 --> 00:50:26.473
Look down the tunnel. Danny. It's lovely.

485
00:50:29.060 --> 00:50:32.521
It's just like Blackpool
at the height of the season.

486
00:50:34.398 --> 00:50:36.900
You ever been to Blackpool. Danny?

487
00:50:37.026 --> 00:50:38.736
Yes.

488
00:50:38.861 --> 00:50:40.821
No.

489
00:50:41.656 --> 00:50:43.574
I don't know.

490
00:50:47.036 --> 00:50:48.996
It's time. Roger.

491
00:51:01.300 --> 00:51:04.803
Bartlett. MacDonald. Ashley-Pitt.

492
00:51:08.474 --> 00:51:09.975
It's all clear. sir.

493
00:51:18.860 --> 00:51:20.820
All set. Roger.

494
00:51:33.374 --> 00:51:35.125
Roger.

495
00:51:35.251 --> 00:51:37.211
Good luck.

496
00:52:08.159 --> 00:52:10.619
They're coming down
the shaft now. Danny.

497
00:52:10.745 --> 00:52:14.206
And then they'll be coming
right up the tunnel.

498
00:52:20.379 --> 00:52:22.422
Willie...

499
00:52:22.548 --> 00:52:25.634
I can't wait. I must get out.

500
00:52:26.052 --> 00:52:29.638
Danny! Danny! Danny! Danny!

501
00:52:57.542 --> 00:53:01.003
What is it. Danny? What's the matter?
Danny! Come here!

502
00:53:01.671 --> 00:53:04.757
Roger? Danny and I'll go later.
We'll take another place.

503
00:53:04.882 --> 00:53:07.885
Danny. tell me what this is
and tell me quickly!

504
00:53:08.010 --> 00:53:12.014
This tunnel is mine as much as anybody.
I dug it. I built it.

505
00:53:12.139 --> 00:53:14.432
I was buried many times.
I go when I want.

506
00:53:14.559 --> 00:53:16.519
Let me out. Let me out.

507
00:53:19.897 --> 00:53:22.190
Take him out. Willie. Take him out.

508
00:53:37.248 --> 00:53:39.208
Danny? What is it?

509
00:53:39.625 --> 00:53:41.752
Danny. what's going on?

510
00:53:41.878 --> 00:53:45.047
It's all right. Sedgwick.
It's all right. We're going later.

511
00:53:51.637 --> 00:53:54.306
Danny. it's all right. It's all right.

512
00:53:54.473 --> 00:53:58.310
We can take another place in the line.
It's all right.

513
00:53:59.020 --> 00:54:00.980
All right. Colin. Down you go.

514
00:54:01.689 --> 00:54:06.402
Sit down. Feel the top rung of
the ladder with your right foot. Got it?

515
00:54:06.527 --> 00:54:08.487
Down you go.

516
00:54:23.836 --> 00:54:25.838
Danny cut out. huh?

517
00:54:26.005 --> 00:54:28.549
Willie took him up top. Hilts. l...

518
00:54:41.687 --> 00:54:44.314
- Remember. keep your head down.
- Right.

519
00:55:01.457 --> 00:55:03.375
Right.

520
00:55:10.341 --> 00:55:12.176
Bartlett.
